features: 【Double Head Desk Lamp, Illuminate More Areas】The RealPlus office lamp features dual swing arms that can be unfolded horizontally up to 180°, as well as 4 adjustable joints to meet your preferred angles. With a height of 17 inches, this lamp effectively disperses light across a wider area, remaining unobstructed by tall objects such as computer monitors.

【USB Charging Port & Enhanced Functionality】This desk lamp is equipped with a built-in USB charging port, ensuring convenient access to charging your phone without worrying about limited outlets. It offers memory function, 10 dimmable brightness levels, 5 color modes (ranging from 3000K to 6000K), a dedicated reading mode, and a 45-minute timer. All these functions are easily accessible through the touch panel – simply touch or swipe to adjust settings.

【15W Adapter and Pen Holder Included】Each package includes a desk lamp, a 15W adapter, a pen holder, a charging cable, a manual, and an anti-skid pad. The anti-skid pad prevents your phone from slipping off the panel. Simply unpack the box, attach the adapter and charging cable to the lamp, and it will work immediately – no need to worry about not having a 15W adapter on hand.

【Eye-Caring LED Desk Light】Our desk light consists of 76 high-quality LEDs that eliminate flickering, providing a gentle and comfortable lighting experience that won’t strain your eyes. With a brightness of up to 750LM, it is suitable for various daily activities such as reading, offering ample brightness without causing eye fatigue.

【Use It In Wherever You Need】Our LED lamp is not limited to the office – it serves as an excellent light source for pianos, dorm rooms, reading areas, bedside tables, architectural workspaces, drawing tables, and more. Its modern design seamlessly blends with any decor or setup, just place it in wherever you need it most.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great reading light with lots of settings
reviews.reviewText: This is a great reading light. I love the modern look of it and it looks great on my nightstand. It also has useful easy settings. Once I turn it on, I can set it as a reading light with one button. If I want to make it a dim night light, I can do that with button settings. It even has a timer so that I can have it automatically turn off after 45 minutes. That is perfect if I fall asleep while reading, which I do all the time.This light is also versitile in that I can move all the parts to make the light show in the direction where I want it to light. It can be a bit bright on the highest setting, so it is nice to move the parts around so the light shines in a good spot.There is a pen holder that I originally thought was a phone holder. It has a plastic divider in the center, so it cannot hold a phone. It would have been nice if it didn't have the plastic divider so that I could choose to hold pens or my phone there.Overall, it is a very good light for reading at night.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Produces and okay amount of light, and has okay adjustments for direction.
reviews.reviewText: This lamp has two lights on arms, which can move up and down and side to side a bit. The lights do not rotate perpendicular to the length of the light, however, which would be really convenient. The lamp is lightweight, for whatever that's worth. There's a USB charging port at the base, which is convenient. The amount of light it produces isn't impressive, but it's enough to be useful. And you can change the color "temperature", to adjust it to your preferences for warm or cold looking light.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Eye-Safe Illumination and Convenience
reviews.reviewText: I've been thoroughly impressed with the RealPlus Double Head Desk Lamp, and it's not just because of its exceptional lighting capabilities. This little lamp is quite the game-changer in terms of style, performance, and convenience.Measuring at 17 inches in height, this desk lamp's size is just right for various applications. It effectively disperses light across a wider area without the possibility of being obstructed by tall objects like computer monitors. The dual swing arms and four adjustable joints are easy to maneuver, allowing you to position the light exactly where you need it, making it perfect for your workspace illumination.Performance-wise, this lamp truly shines. With 76 high-quality LEDs, it eliminates flickering and provides a gentle, comfortable lighting experience that won't strain your eyes. This lamp also offers up to 750LM of brightness, making it suitable for various daily activities like reading, working, or simply providing ample illumination without causing eye fatigue.Assembling the RealPlus Desk Lamp was a breeze. The package includes a 15W adapter, a pen holder, charging cable, manual, and an anti-skid pad. No need to worry about not having a 15W adapter on hand; it's all included. Simply unpack the box, attach the adapter and charging cable to the lamp, and it's ready to use.Lastly, the lamp's versatility is remarkable. It's not limited to the office; it's an excellent light source for pianos, dorm rooms, reading areas, bedside tables, architectural workspaces, drawing tables, and more. Its modern design seamlessly blends with any decor or setup, making it a valuable addition wherever you need it most.In conclusion, the RealPlus Double Head Desk Lamp is a quality made multifunctional lighting solution that not only will impress you with its performance, convenience, and style but also the value of product you will receive for your money! If you're seeking an upgrade to your current lighting setup, this lamp comes highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Compact, Plenty of light for a homework desk.
reviews.reviewText: I liked that it has adjustable arms so you can cover more area with light. It has adjustments for color temperature and brightness. It advertises a slider for brightness adjustment, but I found it easier to just tap at the brightness level you need. Brightness seems good, they advertise 750 lumens. I think that it is probably accurate as it seems brighter than a 500 lu worklight that I have. One problem that I had was It would fall over if I leaned the light too far from vertical. They say that it can be leaned forward but I found that the base did not have enough weight to support that. Once you leaned the light 15~20 degrees from vertical the lamp will just fall over.It also features a USB port for charging, but it is only a 10w charger so it's not too useful for charging a phone. Something low power like some earbuds or a headset will be fine but not a phone.It comes with it's own USB power adapter and cable.It would be 5 stars if it did not fall over, but I still like the light.
